text: South Grade School Building, also known as the Administration Building, Twin Lakes School Corporation, is a historic two-room school building located at Monticello, White County, Indiana. It was built in 1892, and is a 1 1/2-story, brick building with a gable on hip roof. It is seven bays wide and has a three bay wide central pedimented pavilion.
